    Information</orgName> and <title xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">The Times</title> for 29 June 1790 lists him as a steward for a fundraising dinner 
      for <persName xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" key="TO01">John Horne Tooke's</persName> election to     the Westminster seat.  A Mr J F Tuffin is mentioned in Bewley, <title xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Gentleman Radical: 
        a life of John Horne Tooke, 1736–1812</title>, as a friend of 
      Horne Tooke's and in connection with the Society for Constitutional Information.
      Godwin notes him as 'Tuffen' in the two 1802 entries but thereafter the spelling is correct.
